<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-F97B00A9-3A97-45AC-986E-5B762C45801F" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-F97B00A9-3A97-45AC-986E-5B762C45801F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">22 The function of Power</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The function of power provides power to the system ? 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Introduction</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Power function has several components necessary to provide power to all parts of the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Below you find a description of the different components. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Input</title><p class="- topic/p ">At the input side there are two mains connections L1 and L2. These 2 lines should be connected to separate groups in the customers fuse box because of the large current required.. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The lines are fed though 4 circuit breakers. (<comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Circuit Breaker</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22Q1 </compcodenr></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Circuit Breaker</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22Q2 </compcodenr></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Circuit Breaker</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22Q3 </compcodenr></comp> / <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Circuit Breaker</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22Q4 </compcodenr></comp>) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Main Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22S1 </compcodenr></comp> switches the power for the system ON or OFF. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">When the main switch is operated</b> : 
</p><ol id="OL_C43BA537803E45B092751D50D82A76D2" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_F2F18120C74546C8942981950AA1AAB7" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The power (L1) is send to the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_F3C6DFC89A2C4A8EA969D30F66E6B002" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> receives power (L1) and will start-up. 
</p></li><li id="LI_9E1512CA70B04AB29B7816B16CCF56B6" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> When the <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> starts up, the 5V standby voltage of the ATX windows powersupply is used to activate a relay on <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> which turns on the mains power for the <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_472B381BF18C40D4A58931EA888C57DF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph> will now start-up and take control of the power distribution. 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The function Power consists of the following parts and functions</title><table id="GUID-257D4C3A-4F85-4FF6-A50B-A5EC3646A48F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Part / Function 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">AC Switch</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA01 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The main function of the AC switch is to allow the <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> and <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph> to switch several mains connected devices ON or OFF. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="22FUNC02" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B9205EDD-83D4-4B18-8943-AC0D69DA8918.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 The function of the AC Switch ( 22PBA01 ;)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp> distributes power throughout the printer, generates feedback signals. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="22FUNC03" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-CA892D7D-7A16-494D-BA90-86FFFAFA0116.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 The function of the Distribution PBA ( 22PBA02 ;)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA03 </compcodenr></comp> provides power to <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Carriage PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 05PBA07 </compcodenr></comp> via the FFC interface. (Flex Foil Cable) 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="22FUNC04" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-5D0DF386-496B-4F1D-A323-318F94B4D58B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 The function of the Printhead Distribution PBA ( 22PBA03 ;)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The safety circuits 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The safety circuits provide a safe environment for the customers. This done by means of the door switches that switch of the dangerous functions. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="22FUNC05" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-27ADD83A-6132-4F17-A35D-698F181C3D6F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 The function of the safety circuits</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_505547C4BC0F4F1B8B5A57A6892E53F5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Also see</title><ul id="UL_2B937589D07A4D968B51A1E088410D2B" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_A574555B90B8416885165C7F3E920D4D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="22COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F9B91945-CB0C-4E4A-AFEB-0B62B0D1872C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 The components of Power</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_CFC8AD6ED7CC40DBAAE02118AFD30824" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="22ELEC02" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-CC38BA75-75BF-4D5C-9B36-6E9BF14C4E16.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 Mains distribution</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_61F14AF3AC1C4A0598562E142BB64FD4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="22ELEC03" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-3D9B4436-92A4-4A52-B8BE-347B7C5D002B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>22 Power supply</xref> 
</p></li></ul></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-B4557947-F0AA-4402-B5B4-34B41260F60F.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
